The paper deals with algorithms for computing a planar morph between two planar straight-line drawings of a plane graph, which involves concepts from computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the optimality of the algorithm, which is related to lower bounds in computational complexity (cs.DM). The problem of morphing planar graphs is a classic problem in graph drawing (cs.GR), and the paper's focus on improving the upper bound for morphing steps and proving optimality fits within this sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of algorithms and computational techniques to solve a problem in graph drawing and geometry also makes it relevant to the sub-category of computational science (cs.SI).
